\b \cf3 \cb4 Customs
\b0 \cf0 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \cb4 At a bal there will be several lines forming, with the leader leading his/her line in some pattern. The leader (person at the left-hand end of the line) will lead the line into a spiral or double it back on itself to form patterns on the dance floor, and allow the dancers to see each other.\cf3 \cb1 \
\cf3 \cb4 An dros often have songs associated with them, and these are usually sung as a verse-chorus or call-response, with the leader singing the verses or calls. The musicians will sometimes play from the middle of the dance floor, and the dancers will then often form a spiral around them.}